1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a model to characterize human perception of JPEG images, which is a common topic in computer vision research. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with modeling human perception of multimedia content, specifically JPEG images. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses the concept of just noticeable differences (JND) to model human perception, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper focuses on modeling human perception of JPEG images, which is relevant to the field of human-computer interaction. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper deals with modeling human perception of visual content, specifically JPEG images, which falls under the domain of computer graphics.
